  "facts": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Poland village, New York, emerged in the 1880s with a church, hotel, grist mill, tannery, and a bootjack & ladder manufacturer.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://villagepoland.digitaltowpathny.gov:10110/content/History"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village also housed two blacksmith shops, a cheese box factory, and a cabinet shop, showcasing its diverse craftsmanship.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://villagepoland.digitaltowpathny.gov:10110/content/History"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Adam Parys, whose parents were Polish immigrants, opened the original Polski Meat Market in the 1990s, starting as a butcher shop.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://worldfootprints.com/compass/north-america/united-states/new-york/greenpoint-brooklyn-a-polish-neighborhood/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Over time, the market grew into a community hub where locals and workers alike gathered for fresh produce and friendly conversation.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://worldfootprints.com/compass/north-america/united-states/new-york/greenpoint-brooklyn-a-polish-neighborhood/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Poland village’s early economy relied heavily on its mills and factories, making it a key industrial spot in the region during the late 19th century.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://villagepoland.digitaltowpathny.gov:10110/content/History"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "House building boomed in Poland village during the 1880s, driven by the influx of workers to its growing factories.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
